new_feature_requests.summary:
In backend/main.mo, inside the initialize() function, locate the case (?_) {} branch that currently short-circuits when the caller already exists in userRoles. Replace only that branch with the following logic — touching nothing else in the file:

case (?_) {
  if (not state.adminAssigned and userProvidedToken == adminToken) {
    state.userRoles.add(caller, #admin);
    state.adminAssigned := true;
  };
};

This allows a principal already registered as #user to be promoted to #admin if and only if the correct admin token is supplied and adminAssigned is still false. All other logic, function signatures, stable variables, and module structure must remain completely unchanged.
